body.val: The order of these two are the main issue that we want the students to realize regarding the happy path (locking is also problematic, that's for the imsc exercise). Basically the problem is that someone can easily lock the places that we unlocked, before we could book them.
things around payment, locking and booking can get into some problematic, inconsistency prone setups - they should find a problematic scenario connected to these

What components send/receive the events on the state machine (from/to Group Trip): - Booking Database: addBooking, deleteBooking, removalDone, bookingDone - Office: openTrip, cancelTrip, deleteTrip - User Handler: bookingRequest, bookingRemovalRequest
Communication inbetween the components is asynchronous.
- bookings always contains the current number of people booked for this trip - capacity is the maximum number of people booked for this trip.
